\"jQuery Query Parser\" plugin here or before this point: \n// https://github.com/mattsnider/jquery-plugin-query-parser\n (function($){var pl=/\\+/g,searchStrict=/([^&=]+)=+([^&]*)/g,searchTolerant=/([^&=]+)=?([^&]*)/g,decode=function(s){return decodeURIComponent(s.replace(pl,\" \"));};$.parseQuery=function(query,options){var match,o={},opts=options||{},search=opts.tolerant?searchTolerant:searchStrict;if('?'===query.substring(0,1)){query=query.substring(1);}while(match=search.exec(query)){o[decode(match[1])]=decode(match[2]);}return VIDEO CODE\njQuery(document).ready(function($){\n  \n// BOOTSTRAP 3.0 - Open YouTube Video Dynamicaly in Modal Window\n// Modal Window for dynamically opening videos\n$('a[href^=\"https://www.youtube.com\"]').on('click', function(e){\n  // Store the query string variables and values\n  // Uses \"jQuery Query Parser\" plugin, to allow for various URL formats (could have extra parameters)\n  var queryString = $(this).attr('href').slice( $(this).attr('href').indexOf('?') + 1);\n  var queryVars = $.parseQuery( queryString );\n \n  // if GET variable \"v\" exists. This is the Youtube Video ID\n  if ( 'v' in queryVars )\n  {\n    // Prevent opening of external page\n    e.preventDefault();\n \n    // Variables for iFrame code. Width and height from data attributes, else use default.\n    var vidWidth = 1280; // default\n    var vidHeight = 720; // default\n    if ( $(this).attr('data-width') ) { vidWidth = parseInt($(this).attr('data-width')); }\n    if ( $(this).attr('data-height') ) { vidHeight =  parseInt($(this).attr('data-height')); }\n    var iFrameCode = '<div class=\"container\"><div class=\"row\"><div class=\"col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1\"><div class=\"video-container\"><iframe width=\"' + vidWidth + '\" height=\"'+ vidHeight +'\" scrolling=\"no\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/'+  queryVars['v'] +'?rel=0&wmode=transparent&showinfo=0&autoplay=0\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></div></div></div></div>';\n \n    // Replace Modal HTML with iFrame Embed\n    $('#mediaModal .modal-body').html(iFrameCode);\n\n \n    // Open Modal\n    $('#mediaModal').modal();\n  }\n});\n \n// Clear modal contents on close. \n// There was mention of videos that kept playing in the background.\n$('#mediaModal').on('hidden.bs.modal', function () {\n  $('#mediaModal .modal-body').html('');\n});\n \n});
